        "authorId" : "554ba0f6-6e6a-40c3-98e0-1a6cc4a8e1c6",
        "body" : "That would fail. EA is not a documented allowed type for the `to_replace` argument of the `replace` method. to be fair, nor is numpy array or tuple. The safest way to restore the old undocumented behavior is to revert #38097, but not sure that a performance hit for users passing the correct type is the way forward.\r\n\r\nAny container, even a list, with numpy scalars will still fail. This is a fix for a specific case for an arguably incorrect usage without a perf hit for correct usage.",
